headline: Gold Prices Climb Closer to $5,000 an Ounce
summary: Gold prices reached another all-time high Friday.    Most actively traded futures traded as high as $4,989.90 a troy ounce, an intraday record, before pulling back to about $4,983.   January futures settled at $4,976.

headline: This Pro Is ‘More and More Bullish’ on Gold. How He’s Playing It.
summary: Gold has been one of the biggest beneficiaries of the financial and geopolitical ructions of the past year, vaulting from one record to the next and soaring nearly 80% from late last January, according to Dow Jones market data.  The events this past week surrounding the U.S. threats of a less-than-friendly takeover of Greenland were only the latest boost to bullion.  For instance, Goldman Sachs this past week hiked its year-end target to $5,400 an ounce from $4,900.

headline: Gold Prices Spike Toward $5,000 an Ounce
summary: Gold prices hit another all-time high early Friday.    Most actively traded futures traded as high as $4,970 a troy ounce, an intraday record, before pulling back to about $4,944.   The metal has jumped roughly 7% so far this week, boosted by Greenland-related geopolitical anxieties.
